Supporting.fact: The fraction slash ⟨ ⁄ ⟩ is used between two numbers to indicate a fraction or ratio. Such formatting developed as a way to write the horizontal fraction bar on a single line of text.
Supporting.title: Slash (punctuation) - Wikipedia

Supporting.fact: It is called a solidus in Unicode, it is also known as an oblique stroke, and it has several other historical or technical names, including oblique and virgule . A slash in the reverse direction \ is known as a backslash . Slashes may be found in early writing as a variant form of dashes, vertical strokes, etc.
Supporting.title: Slash (punctuation) - Wikipedia
